```

 - If the keys are static, then you can make it even better (credit to this [thread](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/45251664/typescript-derive-union-type-from-tuple-array-values))

```
const keys = [&#39;key1&#39;, &#39;key2&#39;, &#39;key3&#39;, &#39;key4&#39;] as const; // TS3.4 syntax
